        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 12:38PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1238 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over La Joya, or 19 miles north of Socorro, moving west at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Joya, Bernardo and Contreras.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 60 between Mile Markers 166 and 167.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 166 and 175.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
